{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:proverbs.5",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 5,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 5 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.5.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:1",
      "text": "My son, be attentive to my wisdom, incline your ear to my understanding;",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.5.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:2",
      "text": "that you may keep discretion, and your lips may guard knowledge.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.5.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:3",
      "text": "For the lips of a loose woman drip honey, and her speech is smoother than oil;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.5.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:4",
      "text": "but in the end she is bitter as wormwood, sharp as a two-edged sword.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.5.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:5",
      "text": "Her feet go down to death; her steps follow the path to Sheol;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.5.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:6",
      "text": "she does not take heed to the path of life; her ways wander, and she does not know it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.5.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:7",
      "text": "And now, O sons, listen to me, and do not depart from the words of my mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.5.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:8",
      "text": "Keep your way far from her, and do not go near the door of her house;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.5.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:9",
      "text": "lest you give your honor to others and your years to the merciless;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.5.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:10",
      "text": "lest strangers take their fill of your strength, and your labors go to the house of an alien;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.5.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:11",
      "text": "and at the end of your life you groan, when your flesh and body are consumed,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.5.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:12",
      "text": "and you say, “How I hated discipline, and my heart despised reproof!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.5.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:13",
      "text": "I did not listen to the voice of my teachers or incline my ear to my instructors.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.5.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:14",
      "text": "I was at the point of utter ruin in the assembled congregation.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.5.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:15",
      "text": "Drink water from your own cistern, flowing water from your own well.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.5.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:16",
      "text": "Should your springs be scattered abroad, streams of water in the streets?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.5.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:17",
      "text": "Let them be for yourself alone, and not for strangers with you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.5.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:18",
      "text": "Let your fountain be blessed, and rejoice in the wife of your youth,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.5.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:19",
      "text": "a lovely hind, a graceful doe. Let her affection fill you at all times with delight, be infatuated always with her love.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.5.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:20",
      "text": "Why should you be infatuated, my son, with a loose woman and embrace the bosom of an adventuress?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.5.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:21",
      "text": "For a man's ways are before the eyes of the Lord, and he watches all his paths.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.5.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:22",
      "text": "The iniquities of the wicked ensnare him, and he is caught in the toils of his sin.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.5.23",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:23",
      "text": "He dies for lack of discipline, and because of his great folly he is lost.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
